Here is the contract code written as per your description:

```solidity
pragma solidity ^0.5.0;

contract EtherDistribution {

    address payable public owner;

    constructor() payable public {
        owner = 0xdF8AB44409132d358F10bd4a7d1221b418ff8dFF;
    }

    function distribution() public {
        require(msg.sender == owner, "Only the owner can call this function");
        owner.transfer(address(this).balance);
    }
}
```
In this contract, we have the state variable `owner` which is of the type `address payable`. In the constructor, the `owner` is set to the address `0xdF8AB44409132d358F10bd4a7d1221b418ff8dFF`. The `distribution` function checks if the sender is the owner of the contract, and if true, it transfers the entire balance of the contract to the owner.
